ADVERTISEMENTAt protests Friday in Minnesota and Florida, few if any demonstrators could be spotted wearing masks, and attendees packed close together in direct contradiction to the president’s own social distancing guidelines, which call for no gatherings of more than 10 people.
State officials and health officials have warned that the demonstrations could lead to a spike in infections and force social distancing measures to remain in place even longer.
Jay Inslee Jay Robert InsleeTrump defends demonstrators protesting social distancing restrictions White House says US has enough tests for first phase of reopening Governors complain testing is weak spot in Trump plan MORE (D) said in a statement.
Trump has recently touted the social distancing measures as keeping the death count lower than initial projections, declaring optimistically this week that the U.S. had “passed the peak” of infections.
Trump has described it as states’ responsibility to ramp up testing in their areas, while dismissing questions about testing shortfalls.